The paper discusses security mechanisms for wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper focuses on the distributed nature of WSNs and their deployment in remote areas, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the resource constraints in sensor nodes, which suggests that it may fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses countermeasures for attacks, which suggests that it may fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the future direction of research in WSN security, which suggests that it may fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
